Subject: Beta Readers' Importance
Description: It made perfect sense when you wrote it, and when you read it. But then someone else says 'Why didn't you look that up?' or 'That's not how that works!' to your chagrin. This is why authors need beta readers. To catch things you miss, to know things you don't -- to see that blind spot.   Speakers include:Anne Zanoni  - Track: Literature  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
